â””â”€â”€ README.md
Key Improvements:
MVC Architecture: Organized into proper Models, Views, and Controllers

Separation of Concerns: Public assets are in /public for better security

Simplified API Structure: Consolidated API endpoints into logical files

Middleware Support: Added middleware for authentication and security

Core Components: Centralized core functionality in /app/core

Storage Optimization: Consolidated logs and cache in /storage

Database Management: All database-related files in /database

Vendor Management: Composer dependencies in /vendor

This structure is more maintainable, follows modern PHP development practices, and provides better security by separating public-facing files from application logic.

